this will set every attribute of an instance of a class (`parent`) to the same-named attribute in a class called `Child`. Note that it will only change attributes in the class `dict`.

    child = Child()
    for att, value in parent.__dict__.items():
        setattr(child, att, value)

You can change almost ALL attributes with this (`__weakref__`), for example will not be change):

    class Test():
        def __init__(self):
            self.t = None
            
    a = Test()
    a.t = &#39;set t&#39;
    a.b = &#39;set b&#39;
    
    class Test2():
        def __init__(self):
            pass
    
    child = Test2()
    for att in dir(a):
        try:
            setattr(child, att, getattr(a,att))
        except AttributeError:
            continue

But, you will also be changing the class of the variable, i.e. `child.__class__ == Test`

