It&#39;s only will happen in `769px-814px` screen widths becase `#Image903 p.text-caption` has `margin-top: 40px;` set. So, you can add a padding top to handle that situation. To fix this, find `@media only screen and (max-width: 900px)` and just add `padding-top: 40px;` to it as below:

    @media only screen and (max-width: 900px)
    #Image903 p.text-caption {
        margin-top: -40px;
        padding-top: 40px;
    }

Without touching any position more than your theme currently does … Really a lot of absolute position use in a bad way for those days.

You could also change the overflow like this :

    #Image903 .about-content {
        overflow: visible;
    }

